017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: I accompanied the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and during travel he would not add more to his prayer than two cycles. Abu Bakr, Umar, and Uthman did likewise, may Allah be pleased with them. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1051, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 689 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19587,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/26\/ghusl-before-eid-prayer\/","url_meta":{"origin":19614,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Eid: Perform Ghusl before attending Eid prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Nafi\u2019 reported: Abdullah ibn Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, used to perform a ritual bath\u00a0on the day of Eid\u00a0before he would depart\u00a0for prayer. Source: al-Muwat\u0323t\u0323a' 609 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Nawawi Imam al-Nawawi commented, \"The narrations of Al-Shafi'i and his companions agree upon the recommendation to perform\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4035,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/03\/fasting-haram-eid-fitr-adha-tashriq\/","url_meta":{"origin":19614,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Eid: The Prophet forbids fasting on the two Eids","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 3, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu 'Ubayd reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cO people, the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, has prohibited you from fasting on the days of these two celebrations, Eid al-Fitr and Eid al-Adha. One of them is the day you break\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33429,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/09\/11\/uthman-third-adhan-jumuah\/","url_meta":{"origin":19614,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Adhan: Uthman institutes third call to prayer on Friday","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 11, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Sa\u2019ib ibn Yazid reported: The announcement of Friday prayer was first made when the Imam would sit upon the pulpit in the time of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, as well as Abu Bakr and Umar, may Allah be pleased with them. In the time of Uthman,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19612,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/26\/no-adhan-eid-nawafil-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":19614,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Eid: No call to prayer for Eid, voluntary prayers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir ibn Samurah reported: I performed the Eid prayers with the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, more than once, without announcing the two calls to prayer. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 887 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim Al-Tirmidhi said, \u201cThis is acted upon by the scholars among\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5037,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/12\/prophet-dates-eid-al-fitr\/","url_meta":{"origin":19614,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Eid: The Prophet eats dates before Eid prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 12, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would not proceed on the day of Eid al-Fitr\u00a0until he had eaten some dates. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 953 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Bukhari \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0643\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/19614","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\